news.title: China property firms' shares, bonds hit as Yango seeks new extension
news.para: Fujian province-based Yango Group Co. Ltd. has been in talks with investors to discuss the extension of payments on yuan-denominated asset-backed securities that holders can redeem this month.

news.title: Demand for home loan coming from all segments of market: Keki Mistry, HDFC
news.para: “The percentage of non-performing loans has come down as we have seen about a 25 to 27 bps improvement in the level of non-performing loans. ”

news.title: Haryana empowers SDMs, city magistrates to register property documents
news.para: CM announced that from Monday onwards all SDMs and City Magistrates in the state shall be designated as Sub-Registrars and Joint Sub-Registrars for the purposes of registration of instruments of transfer of properties etc.

news.title: Locals stage protest at Dehradun civic body office over defective streetlights
news.para: "Even when the streetlights work, there have been maintenance issues. We had filed a complaint eight days back, but the problem was not addressed and even after assurance by corporation officials,” said Bhupendra Kathait, city councillor.

news.title: Pune civic body developing software to run Gunthewari scheme online
news.para: “It will help in detecting fake documents and curbing scheme misuse,” said Yuvraj Deshmukh, a senior official of Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC)’s building permissions department.

news.title: Chandigarh administration to take call on land pooling policy next week: Adviser
news.para: UT adviser Dharam Pal said earlier, the meeting was scheduled for Wednesday, but now the final decision will be taken next week, when UT and MC officials will review the proposal of the Bengaluru-based Indian Institute of Human Settlement (IIHS).

news.title: Gujarat CM allots 560 government flats in Gandhinagar
news.para: A total of 560 quarters – 280 each of the B and C type – have been constructed by the roads and buildings department at a cost of Rs 149.8 crore.

news.title: Madras HC issues notice on sand mining in Thamirabarani river
news.para: ​The petitioner stated that a few people own brick kilns near the riverbed at Sriparankusanallur village in Srivaikuntam taluk. Most of the kilns are functioning illegally without obtaining proper permission.

news.title: Only auction can ensure uniformity in leasing of municipal properties: HC
news.para: The observation was made while directing Arkalgud town panchayat in Hassan district to auction all the 112 shops under its control by issuing a fresh notification.

news.title: Kolkata records 39,832 property registrations between Jan-Oct 2021
news.para: As many as 39,832 property registrations were completed in Kolkata between January and October, a little more than double the number (19,876) of the corresponding period last year.

news.title: Bombay HC declines further protection to builder in urban land ceiling scam
news.para: The builder had filed a pre-arrest bail application, and Justice S P Tavade, vacation judge at the HC, on Monday said it appears that the court had not extended the interim order earlier, and that a bench had recused itself on October 27.

news.title: Moody's upgrades Macrotech Developers' to B3 on debt reduction, sales improvement
news.para: "The upgrade of MDL's ratings to B3 from Caa1 reflects an improvement in the company's credit profile as a result of debt reduction measures by the management, as well as a strong recovery in the company's operating performance both at India and London following the easing of pandemic-related restrictions,” said Sweta Patodia, a Moody's Analyst.

news.title: Madhuri Dixit-Nene leases 5,500 sq ft apartment in Mumbai's Worli
news.para: In the first year, Madhuri will be paying monthly rental of Rs 12.50 lakh taking the annual pay out to Rs 1.5 crore. In total, she will be paying rent of nearly 4.73 crore over the entire tenure of three years including the rental escalation agreed upon.

news.title: Smart cities mission, PMAY, RERA to be studied by parliamentary panel
news.para: The standing committee will examine and report during the term 2021-22 on improving the standard and quality of living in urban cities- air quality, sewage treatment and drainage system, traffic management etc.

news.title: Citibank to offer lease rental discounting for commercial real estate companies
news.para: LRD is a globally popular credit instrument offered against rental receipts. This will likely ease the funds crunch in the real estate sector, hit hard by the pandemic. The bank will be setting up a separate team and infrastructure for this service line.
